==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*berga-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[berg]] (Dutch [[berg]]), Old High German [[berg]] (German [[Berg]]), Old Norse [[bjarg]] (Swedish [[berg]]), Gothic 𐌱𐌰𐌹𐍂𐌲-.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /beorg/

===Noun===
'''beorg''' ''m''
# a [[hill]] or [[mountain]]
#:''Oþ ða beorgas ðe man hæt Alpis'': to the mountains that are called the Alps.  (Orosius)
# a [[mound]], a heap of stones, a [[barrow]]


